{"id": 50, "ts": 1778840908.456435, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_1", "message": "I have reviewed all the attributes we possess for each candidate.\u202fOnly Candidate\u202fB has explicit evidence of the two non\u2011negotiable qualities for long\u2011distance operations: **100\u202f% reliability** and the ability to **stay calm in a crisis**.\u202fB also brings strong technical skills (weather assessment, computer proficiency) that directly support safe international flights.\nThe other candidates lack any documented reliability or calm\u2011under\u2011pressure evidence.\u202fCandidate\u202fA shows excellent situational awareness and leadership but has no proven reliability or stress\u2011management record and also has interpersonal/health concerns.\u202fCandidate\u202fC handles stress well and creates a positive crew atmosphere, yet we have no reliability data and C has communication and growth issues.\u202fCandidate\u202fD solves problems and takes responsibility seriously, but again there is no reliability or calmness evidence, and D is described as arrogant and moody.\nWhile B\u2019s interpersonal drawbacks (pretentious tone, grumpiness, occasional nasty remarks, weak numeric memory) are noted, they do not outweigh the absence of the core safety attributes in the other candidates. Therefore, based on the available facts, Candidate\u202fB best satisfies the essential criteria for the long\u2011distance pilot role.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
